        "slug": "battered-but-strong",
        "status": "publish",
        "type": "post",
        "link": "https://www.quarant9.life/poetry/battered-but-strong/",
        "title": {
            "rendered": "Battered But Strong"
        },
        "content": {
            "rendered": "\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Slipping through tiny<br>gaps in my armour,<br>Bruised and battered,<br>I stood myself<br>shoulder to shoulder.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Concealed from the melee<br>of the outside world,<br>It was all harrowing,<br>heartening and humbling<br>discomfort.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">At times it is<br>alarming impulsivity,<br>at others it is<br>frightening<br>compulsivity.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">My internal demons<br>rendering me dumb,<br>Gruesome innards of<br>mental illness that<br>made me succumb.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">There were torments,<br>sufferings and<br>unpleasant bits,<br>but my Depression made<br>me realise how good<br>days fits,<br>and my Anxiety made me<br>sensitive to how<br>others&#8217; feel.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">There were moments I<br>was marooned, helpless<br>on the rocks,<br>But then, there were<br>moments in which I<br>rose, felt the sun on<br>my face, tasted the<br>salt on my lips and<br>stood on my legs,<br>that are<br>BATTERED BUT STRONG!</p>\n",
            "protected": false
        },
        "excerpt": {
            "rendered": "<p>Conversations about mental health are increasing but we still seldom hear what it is like to suffer from mental illness. I feel mental health is discussed more and more these days and yet still no one really understands. This is mental illness &#8211; It is the journey not the time and we are not mere sufferers but there are also the moments where we rose! So read this poem to understand a bit more &#8211; BATTERED BUT STRONG!</p>\n",
            "protected": false
        },
