        "modified": "2020-08-28T12:05:46",
        "modified_gmt": "2020-08-28T12:05:46",
        "slug": "waiting-for-forever",
        "status": "publish",
        "type": "post",
        "link": "https://www.quarant9.life/poetry/waiting-for-forever/",
        "title": {
            "rendered": "Waiting for Forever"
        },
        "content": {
            "rendered": "\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">The loving heart,<br>Creeping soul,<br>Lost in wounded thoughts.<br>The ignorance and aloneness complementing altogether.<br>That chocolate&#8217;s bitterness and sweetness I can fell &#8217;em together<br>To me you were like a cafe at a midnight Vacant and happy,<br>Sweat and quite.<br>You looked perfect,<br>With feathered or an open hairs.<br>We were good at that instant<br>Just like a cigarette before lighting,<br>You liked my every nick<br>Even my unrhymed poetry.<br>Let us clear this mess,<br>Let&#8217;s have a deal<br>Let&#8217;s stay apart,<br>By staying on the same boat.</p>\n",
            "protected": false
        },
        "excerpt": {
            "rendered": "<p>How do you know when you love someone? I think it&#8217;s when they make you see the beauty in things you once thought were ordinary. But, what if u don&#8217;t want to stay with them. Maybe the poet is so afraid of the situation he will have to face after losing her. That&#8217;s why he chooses to miss her, instead of screaming for her.</p>\n",
            "protected": false
        },
